THERE are many financial setbacks that require you to managing your money. SunMoney spoke to John Manyike, head of financial education at Old Mutual to get you some advice. Manyike said families have been hard hit by the increases in the fuel price and electricity, as well as the VAT. “It is more important than ever to become money smart to ensure you survive till month end and start reducing your debt.” Here are Manyike’s tips for a shockproof household budget: 1 Commit to a budget 2 Cut your transport costs 3 Keep your family healthy 4 Quit bad habits 5 Stay up to date 6 Keep saving 7 Don’t live to impress 8 Learn to say NO!